&lt;p&gt;ClassPass offers thousands of fitness and wellness experiences worldwide, helping people lead active, balanced lifestyles. Our platform makes discovering and enjoying activities simple, personalized, and joyful—whether it&#39;s fitness classes, self-care sessions, a healthy lunch, or a new adventure. Join us in shaping healthier, more vibrant communities around the globe.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role You’ll Play:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Field Account Executive to help rapidly scale our gym footprint. The Field Account Executive will join as a key member of the Field Sales Team, responsible for working with fitness providers from start to finish, including researching new opportunities, initial outreach, contract negotiations, and ensuring a smooth transition for onboarding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will proactively research and connect with fitness providers via phone, email, social media, and industry events to build meaningful partnerships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;You will stay ahead of the competitive landscape by understanding pricing and product differentiators, enabling you to clearly communicate ClassPass’s unique value.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will own the full sales cycle—from generating leads and prospecting, to pitching, negotiating pricing,and executing contracts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will collaborate closely with operations and marketing to keep communications consistent and ensure every partner’s onboarding is a success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will keep Salesforce up to date with accurate and timely information to support growth and strategic decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Experience You’ll Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Entrepreneurial self-starter who thrives in fast-paced, evolving environments and confidently navigates ambiguity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized and adaptable, with the ability to manage multiple priorities effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open-minded problem solver who approaches challenges creatively and develops innovative solutions for partner needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of B2B sales experience with a proven track record of exceeding monthly targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and interpersonal skills, including cold calling, active listening, and building rapport through empathy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced in using Salesforce and email marketing tools to optimize and scale sales workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative team player who works cross-functionally, shares knowledge, and partners effectively with internal teams and external vendors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passionate about fitness and wellness; existing relationships with fitness providers are a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Located in or available to work remotely in: Austin, Boston, Dallas, Miami, Washington, DC, Los Angeles, or San Francisco&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willing to travel up to 30% domestically (possibility of some international travel)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
